name: The number of non-unitary prime divisors of the n-th biquadratefree number that is not cubefree.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
mathematica: f[k_] := If[k == 1, Nothing, Module[{e = FactorInteger[k][[;; , 2]]}, If[Max[e] == 3, Count[e, _?(# > 1 &)], Nothing]]]; Array[f, 1000]
program: (PARI) list(lim) = {my(e); for(k = 2, lim, e = factor(k)[, 2]; if(vecmax(e) == 3, print1(#select(x -> x > 1, e), ", ")));}
author: _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 10 2025

name: The number of non-unitary prime divisors of the n-th cubefree number that is not squarefree.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
mathematica: f[k_] := If[k == 1, Nothing, Module[{e = FactorInteger[k][[;; , 2]]}, If[Max[e] == 2, Count[e, 2], Nothing]]]; Array[f, 150]
program: (PARI) list(lim) = {my(e); for(k = 2, lim, e = factor(k)[, 2]; if(vecmax(e) == 2, print1(#select(x -> x == 2, e), ", ")));}
author: _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 10 2025

name: The number of non-unitary prime divisors of the n-th biquadratefree number that is not squarefree.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
mathematica: f[k_] := If[k == 1, Nothing, Module[{e = FactorInteger[k][[;; , 2]]}, If[2 <= Max[e] <= 3, Count[e, _?(# > 1 &)], Nothing]]]; Array[f, 1000]
program: (PARI) list(lim) = {my(e, emax); for(k = 2, lim, e = factor(k)[, 2]; emax = vecmax(e); if(emax > 1 && emax < 4, print1(#select(x -> x > 1, e), ", ")));}
author: _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 10 2025
